--- !u!114 &224054226
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 224054222}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 6f3fc1dae71b44d48a5ece0732cc4724, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::Exploration1_1
  dialogueScript: {fileID: 224054224}
  playerMovementScript: {fileID: 378410730}
  DialogueLines:
  - I sigh as I gently close my journal and look up to see my surroundings. The living
    room feels homey, its walls decorated with portraits, with woodcraft for ventanilla
    and capiz windows from the 1860s
  - "\u201CWell, that's what it used to be\u2026 Now it's just muddied, destroyed,
    and worn down.\u201D "
  - "Hearing the news about Malabon\u2019s precious heritage zone being severely
    flooded the moment I woke up really put me on edge. Seeing what was left made
    my heart sink."
  - "I decided to become a historian so I can study the conservation of international
    history, but the Raymundo house\u2026 I left it as is despite my parents saying
    it had belonged to one of our distant relatives."
  - "And right now I\u2019m standing inside the living room, seeing it destroyed
    alongside the other remaining heritage houses. I couldn't help but feel like
    I had failed my mission as the house\u2019s caretaker and historian, even though
    the flooding wasn\u2019t my fault."
  - "\u201CThere\u2019s no use moping what\u2019s done is done. I might as well find
    anything left that is worth salvaging in this mess.\u201D "
  DialogueSpeakers:
  - 
  - Aleks
  - 
  - 
  - 
  - Aleks
  restrictionPoints: 0000000006000000
  hasInteractedArtifact1: 0
  hasInteractedArtifact2: 0
  hasInteractedArtifact3: 0
  DialogueLines2:
  - "That\u2019s all there is to salvage."
  - Well, technically, most of these are barely salvageable, as some are clinging
    on to dear life.
  - "After sorting through all salvageable artifacts, there was nothing left to do
    but make sure that they\u2019re stored in a safer place."
  DialogueSpeakers2:
  - Aleks
  - Aleks
  - Aleks
